import libraries

library(raster)

library(car)
## Loading required package: carData

import data

rastblast <-raster("/Users/lavran_pagano/Downloads/Nan_as_0_masked_ham_chms/fixedmasked320320split1.tif")#read in raster
## Warning in showSRID(uprojargs, format = "PROJ", multiline = "NO"): Discarded
## datum Unknown based on GRS80 ellipsoid in CRS definition
Mastersheet<- read.csv('/Users/lavran_pagano/Downloads/Lidar_Training_Data/Lidar_Training_Data.csv')#read in training data
LogMastersheet <-log(Mastersheet[,c(1,4,5,6)])# log transform the data and in clude only the indepnedent and dependent varibles

plot CHM

plot(rastblast)

make an agragated raster with the max height,90th percentile, and 80th percentile for every 133 pixels given the spatial resultion

maxheightrast<-aggregate(rastblast, fact=133, fun=function(i, na.rm) quantile(i, probs=1, na.rm=na.rm))#make a max hight raster also used for extent later
## Warning in showSRID(uprojargs, format = "PROJ", multiline = "NO"): Discarded
## datum Unknown based on GRS80 ellipsoid in CRS definition
percent100<-as.data.frame(maxheightrast)#convert to dataframe
percent90<-as.data.frame(aggregate(rastblast, fact=133, fun=function(i, na.rm) quantile(i, probs=0.90, na.rm=na.rm)))#convert to dataframe
## Warning in showSRID(uprojargs, format = "PROJ", multiline = "NO"): Discarded
## datum Unknown based on GRS80 ellipsoid in CRS definition
percent80<-as.data.frame(aggregate(rastblast, fact=133, fun=function(i, na.rm) quantile(i, probs=0.80, na.rm=na.rm)))#convert to dataframe
## Warning in showSRID(uprojargs, format = "PROJ", multiline = "NO"): Discarded
## datum Unknown based on GRS80 ellipsoid in CRS definition

combine dataframes and logtransform/clean the dataframe

rastdataframe<-data.frame(Height_Max=percent100,Height_90th=percent90,Height_80th=percent80)
colnames(rastdataframe)[1]<-"Height_Max"#rename
colnames(rastdataframe)[2]<-"Height_90th"#rename
colnames(rastdataframe)[3]<-"Height_80th"#rename
lograstdataframe<-log(rastdataframe)# log transform
is.na(lograstdataframe)<-sapply(lograstdataframe, is.infinite)#change -Inif to NA
lograstdataframe[is.na(lograstdataframe)]<-0 #change NA to 0

create a model and check that our model meets the necesasry assumptions

powerlaw<-lm(Biomass ~ Height_Max + Height_80th + Height_90th,data=LogMastersheet)#create model
shapiro.test(residuals(powerlaw))
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  residuals(powerlaw)
## W = 0.96995, p-value = 0.1384
ncvTest(powerlaw)
## Non-constant Variance Score Test 
## Variance formula: ~ fitted.values 
## Chisquare = 0.738945, Df = 1, p = 0.39
summary(powerlaw)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = Biomass ~ Height_Max + Height_80th + Height_90th,

##

apply model to aggragated rasters

logbiodata<-predict(powerlaw,lograstdataframe)

backtransform and get biomass estimates in a dataframe with corosponding cordinates

biodata<-exp(logbiodata)# convert from loged kg to kg
cord<-coordinates(maxheightrast)#get cordinates of the agragated rasters
bioraster<-as.data.frame(cord)# attach cordinates to a data
bioraster$Biomass <-biodata # attach biomass estimates to the dataframe

create biomass raster

bioraster<-rasterFromXYZ(bioraster) #Convert first two columns as lon-lat and third as biomass
rastcrs<-crs(rastblast)#get cordinate refrence system of imput raster
crs(bioraster)<-rastcrs#atach cordinate refrence system of imput raster

check out our biomass raster

plot(bioraster)

###Write biomass raster to working directory

setwd("/Users/lavran_pagano/Downloads/HamltonbiomassCHMs")
writeRaster(bioraster,"biomass320320split1.tif",overwrite=TRUE)
